{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015oVet9xXq9qkGx8X5Tsk3u","type":"tool_result","content":"The elastic user password must be rotated.\n\nOBSERVED STATE:\n- Secret elastic-password contains the current password.\n- Secret elastic-password-next contains the new password.\n- An auth-checker deployment is expected to stay healthy.\n\nYOUR TASK:\n- Rotate the elastic user password to match elastic-password-next.\n- Update the elastic-password secret to the new value.\n- Ensure auth-checker becomes healthy after the rotation.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Do not install CRDs or use operators.\n- Avoid prolonged downtime.\n\nGOAL:\n- Old password fails, new password succeeds.\n- auth-checker is Ready.===PRECOND===\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n7\n\n[precondition:es_next_password_secret_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'es_next_password_secret_fixture':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password-next >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo present\n\n[precondition:es_next_password_secret_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'es_next_password_secret_fixture':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n elasticsearch create secret generic elastic-password-next --from-literal=password=elasticpass-elastic-password-next --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -'\nsecret/elastic-password-next created\n\n[precondition:es_next_password_secret_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'es_next_password_secret_fixture':verify] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password-next >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo present\npresent\n\n[precondition:es_prev_password_configmap_fixture:preconditionUnits[2] 'es_prev_password_configmap_fixture':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get configmap elastic-password-prev >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo present\n\n[precondition:es_prev_password_configmap_fixture:preconditionUnits[2] 'es_prev_password_configmap_fixture':apply] $ /bin/sh -c '\nCUR=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null)\n[ -n \"$CUR\" ] || CUR=elasticpass-old\nkubectl -n elasticsearch create configmap elastic-password-prev --from-literal=password=\"$CUR\" --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n'\n\nconfigmap/elastic-password-prev created\n\n[precondition:es_prev_password_configmap_fixture:preconditionUnits[2] 'es_prev_password_configmap_fixture':verify] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get configmap elastic-password-prev >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo present\npresent\n\n[precondition:es_auth_checker_deployment_fixture:preconditionUnits[3] 'es_auth_checker_deployment_fixture':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get deployment auth-checker >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo present\n\n[precondition:es_auth_checker_deployment_fixture:preconditionUnits[3] 'es_auth_checker_deployment_fixture':apply] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch apply -f cases/elasticsearch/rotate-elastic-password/resource/auth-checker.yaml\ndeployment.apps/auth-checker created\n\n[precondition:es_auth_checker_deployment_fixture:preconditionUnits[3] 'es_auth_checker_deployment_fixture':verify] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get deployment auth-checker >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo present\npresent","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc28f764-57d0-41f2-87f4-3d4dcd9fe662","uuid":"f9ec906f-bf7a-4d5d-8407-c0ad43aed233","timestamp":"2026-06-18T13:13:44.814Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"The elastic user password must be rotated.\n\nOBSERVED STATE:\n- Secret elastic-password contains the current password.\n- Secret elastic-password-next contains the new password.\n- An auth-checker deployment is expected to stay healthy.\n\nYOUR TASK:\n- Rotate the elastic user password to match elastic-password-next.\n- Update the elastic-password secret to the new value.\n- Ensure auth-checker becomes healthy after the rotation.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Do not install CRDs or use operators.\n- Avoid prolonged downtime.\n\nGOAL:\n- Old passw