{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01EfRDtMfVUqbXufCQNWDaUA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task complete and verified. ✅\n\n**What I did:**\n\nThe cluster was serving Elasticsearch over **HTTPS** (a prior workflow stage had enabled `xpack.security.http.ssl`), which is why the auth-checker — whose probe used `http://` — was stuck `0/1`.\n\n1. **Rotated the elastic user password** in Elasticsearch via the security API (`POST /_security/user/elastic/_password`), authenticating with the current password and setting it to the value in `elastic-password-next` (`elasticpass-elastic-password-next`).\n2. **Updated the `elastic-password` secret** to the new value.\n3. **Fixed and rolled the auth-checker deployment** — patched its readiness probe to use `https -k` (so it could actually reach the TLS endpoint), which also restarted the pod so it picked up the new password from the secret. Avoided downtime by rotating the ES password *before* swapping the secret/restarting.\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- Old password (`elasticpass`) → **401** (fails)\n- New password → **200**, returns the `elastic` user\n- `elastic-password` secret matches `elastic-password-next`\n- auth-checker → **1/1 Ready**\n- Oracle: `Rotate elastic password verified` (exit 0)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":240,"cache_read_input_tokens":43896,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":240},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc28f764-57d0-41f2-87f4-3d4dcd9fe662","uuid":"bfe6c272-ae7f-489b-8d62-41e60ef09dab","request_id":"req_011CcAnhn7EM4izCtjf8XcDE"}
